<p>The Christian belief is that Jesus (A.S.) died for the sins of all humanity. That is, the Messiah is supposed to be the blood sacrifice necessary for the forgiveness of sin; in other words, a human sacrifice.</p>
<div class="investigation">    
    <ol>
        <li>
            <span>
                Is human sacrifice necessary for the forgiveness of sin, why God (the Father) disagree to this when Moses wants to offer himself as atonement for his peaple?
                <div class="bible-wrapper">
                    <div class="bible-verse">
                        <div class="bible-hebrew">
